{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Pavlova","content":["Preheat oven to 150°C. Line 2 large baking trays (40 x 35 cm) with baking paper. Trace 2 circles (approx. 20 cm) on the underside of each piece of baking paper, then set baking trays aside.","Place 200 g of the white sugar into mixing bowl and mill <nobr>15 sec\/speed 9<\/nobr>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside.","Place remaining 130 g white sugar into mixing bowl and mill <nobr>15 sec\/speed 9<\/nobr>. Transfer into bowl with the previous batch and set aside. Thoroughly clean and dry mixing bowl."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place egg whites and cream of tartar into mixing bowl and whip <nobr>5 min\/37°C\/speed 3.5<\/nobr>, without measuring cup.","With butterfly whisk still in place, mix <nobr>5 min\/37°C\/speed 3<\/nobr>, slowly adding reserved icing sugar through hole in mixing bowl lid 1 spoon at a time until well combined.","With butterfly whisk still in place, mix <nobr>30-40 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr>, adding vinegar, vanilla, cornflour and ginger through hole in mixing bowl lid until combined.","Spoon mixture into traced circles on baking paper to form discs approx. 4-6 cm thick. Bake for 10 minutes (150°C), then reduce oven temperature to 120°C and bake for 1 hour (120°C).","Turn oven off and allow pavlova discs to cool completely with the oven door shut (approx. 3 hours or overnight). Clean and dry mixing bowl and butterfly whisk."]},{"title":"Toffee syrup","content":["Place all toffee syrup ingredients into mixing bowl and cook <nobr>5 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<\/nobr>, placing simmering basket instead of measuring cup onto mixing bowl lid.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then repeat cooking <nobr>5 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<\/nobr>, placing simmering basket instead of measuring cup onto mixing bowl lid. Transfer into a bowl and set aside. Clean and dry mixing bowl."]},{"title":"Mascarpone cream","content":["Crumble gingerbread or gingernut biscuits into bite-sized pieces in a bowl and set aside."," <strong>Re-insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place cream into mixing bowl and whip <nobr>until soft peaks form\/speed 3.5<\/nobr>. Take care not to overwhip your cream, watch cream carefully through hole in mixing bowl lid.","Add mascarpone and ginger and mix <nobr>2-5 sec\/speed 2<\/nobr>, or until just combined.","To assemble pavlova stack, place 1 of the pavlova discs onto a serving plate or platter. Top disc with half of the mascarpone cream, then decorate with half of the banana slices, half of the nectarine slices (optional), half of the reserved ginger biscuit pieces and 1-2 tablespoons reserved toffee syrup. Place remaining pavlova disc on top, then repeat layering process with remaining mascarpone cream, remaining banana, remaining nectarine (optional), remaining gingerbread pieces and 1-2 tablespoons of the toffee syrup. Serve immediately."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Pavlova","content":["330 g white sugar","250 g egg whites (approx. 8 egg whites), room temperature","1 pinch cream of tartar","1 tsp white vinegar","1 tsp natural vanilla extract","2 tbsp cornflour","2 tsp ground ginger"]},{"title":"Toffee syrup","content":["80 g unsalted butter, cut into pieces","130 g double cream","100 g brown sugar"]},{"title":"Mascarpone cream","content":["100 g gingerbread biscuits","350 g pouring (whipping) cream","250 g mascarpone cheese","1 - 2 tsp ground ginger","2 bananas, peeled and cut into slices, for garnishing","2 nectarines, stones removed and cut into slices, for garnishing (optional)"]}],"id":"r89818","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-u1T2n-b9fPM\/XZaux8S3UXI\/AAAAAAAAhms\/uYplFEQM2n0dY1bkqhlmL9N7rpnStDLoQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_-iJ5ds37DAOqCxyk.png","title":"Gingerbread pavlova stack","publishedAt":"2015-12-14T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"6 g","fat":"29 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"50 g","calories":"1996 kJ \/ 475 kcal"},"usefulItems":"2 baking trays (40 x 35 cm), baking paper, serving platter, oven","hintsAndTricks":["You can replace the mascarpone cheese with extra cream if you prefer."],"basicInfo":["medium","30m","5h 30m","12 portions"]}